### Description

Red Hat developer Stacey Mosier reports that the Javascript example in the Securing Apps guide is not printing errors.  

https://www.keycloak.org/docs/latest/securing_apps/index.html#_javascript_adapter

She suggests it can be updated to use console.error instead of alert:

```js
keycloak.init(options)
  .then(function(authenticated) {
    console.log('rh_keycloak:' + (authenticated ? 'authenticated' : 'not authenticated'));
  }).catch((error) => {
    for (const property in error) {
    console.error(`${property}: ${error[property]}`);
  }
});
```

